<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-005-031 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 585 274</DOCID><JOURNAL>Lotus  Dec 1991 v7 n12 p57(5).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Get a head start on worksheet development; an accountant and 1-2-3veteran shares his ideas for taking the sweat out ofspreadsheeting. (Tutorial)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Schmidt, Walter C.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Almost all work groups using Lotus Development Corp's 1-2-3 orSymphony spreadsheet packages develop conventions and standardsfor worksheet models, and many also create several hard-diskdirectories for various groups of worksheets.andP;  After identifyingthe repetitive aspects of a work group's worksheets, they can beautomated by using simple macros, and the settings used in mostworksheets can be saved in templates that can be used to developnew models.andP;  A model-building worksheet is presented that usesmacros to create dividing lines, to record the date of the mostrecent worksheet update, and to automate printing.andP;  The worksheetpresented serves as a template holding non-standard globalsettings, but it is also a self-running macro that can save theworksheet under a new name without overwriting an existing file;the design and use of the worksheet is described.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   Lotus 1-2-3 (Spreadsheet software) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Form OverlaySpreadsheetsMacrosTutorialProgramming InstructionEnd UsersModels.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>